# Code Quality and Logic Preservation Rule

The redesign is primarily visual.

Do not break existing functionality.

## Preserve

Preserve:

- auth API calls;
- login submission;
- registration submission;
- validation;
- errors;
- loading states;
- routing;
- state management;
- password visibility logic;
- existing localization;
- tests;
- existing environment configuration.

## Do Not

Do not:

- rewrite backend contracts;
- change API endpoints;
- change route names unless required;
- remove validation;
- remove error display;
- remove accessibility;
- introduce unrelated libraries;
- rewrite unrelated pages;
- create duplicated components;
- hardcode repeated design values;
- use inline styles without reason;
- leave dead old CSS.

## Architecture

Prefer reusable components:

```txt
components/auth/
  AuthLayout
  AuthCard
  AuthBrand
  AuthInput
  PasswordInput
  PrimaryButton
  AuthLink
  RememberMeCheckbox
  RegistrationProgress
```

Do not over-engineer, but avoid duplicated login/register UI.

## SOLID / DRY

Follow:

- single responsibility per component;
- reusable shared components;
- design tokens instead of repeated magic values;
- project styling conventions;
- clear naming;
- no unrelated side effects.

## Styling Stack

Use the styling approach already used by the project:

- Tailwind if project uses Tailwind;
- CSS Modules if project uses CSS Modules;
- SCSS if project uses SCSS;
- styled-components if project uses styled-components.

Do not introduce a new styling system unless necessary.
